Melt butter in large saucepan over medium heat. Saute onion and celery 2 to 3 minutes or until softened. Stir in flour until no lumps remain. Stir in potatoes, sausage and broth until well mixed. Bring to boiling; reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir in cream and heat until hot but not boiling. Ladle into soup bowls.